          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Copper toxicity- Menke&rsquo;s Kinky-hair syndrome</span></span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">A 50-year-old man, who recently arrived in India from China for a vacation, visits a local hospital complaining of diarrhea, vomiting, and an unusually rapid heartbeat. He mentions that these symptoms started a few days after his arrival. The attending cardiologist performs an ECG, which indicates arrhythmia, and an echocardiogram, which shows cardiac enlargement. Based on the patient&#39;s clinical presentation and the investigations, which of the following nutrient deficiencies and associated disorders is most likely to be affecting this patient?</span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q5250103",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 30588,
      "difficulty_level": "beginner",
      "subjects_id": [
        1
      ],
      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ans. A) Selenium deficiency- Keshan disease</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option A:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Selenium </strong>is an important <strong>trace element </strong>with <strong>normal </strong>serum level ranges from <strong>50&ndash;100 mg/dL</strong>.</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Impairments </strong>in human <strong>selenoproteins </strong>have been implicated in <strong>tumorigenesis, atherosclerosis and selenium deficiency cardiomyopathy (Keshan disease), </strong>characterized by <strong>multifocal myocardial necrosis, cardiac arrythmias and cardiac enlargement. </strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Isolated <strong>selenium deficiency </strong>results in <strong>liver necrosis, cirrhosis, cardiomyopathy and muscular dystrophy. </strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Selenium <strong>toxicity </strong>is called <strong>Selenosis</strong>, symptoms include <strong>hair loss, falling of nails, diarrhea, weight loss, </strong>and <strong>garlicky odor </strong>in breath. </span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Kashin-beck disease</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"> is characterized by<strong> degenerative osteoarthrosis. </strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Explanation:</span></u></strong><u> </u></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option B. Copper deficiency - Wilson disease</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">: <strong>Incorrect </strong>because <strong>Wilson&#39;s disease</strong> is caused by <strong>copper accumulation,</strong> not deficiency.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option C. Selenium deficiency</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"> - <strong>Acrodermatitis enteropathica</strong>:<strong> Incorrect</strong> because <strong>Acrodermatitis enteropathica</strong> is associated with <strong>zinc deficiency</strong>, <strong>not </strong>selenium.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option D. Copper toxicity</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"> - <strong>Menkes Kinky-hair syndrome</strong>: <strong>Incorrect</strong> as <strong>Menkes disease</strong> is a disorder of <strong>copper deficiency</strong>, not toxicity, and it typically presents in <strong>infancy with brittle</strong>, <strong>kinky hair</strong>, <strong>growth failure</strong>, and <strong>developmental delay,</strong> <strong>not</strong> primarily with cardiac symptoms.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Educational Objective:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Keshan disease </strong>is a <strong>cardiomyopathy</strong> caused by <strong>selenium deficiency</strong>. It is characterized by <strong>multifocal myocardial necrosis </strong>leading to <strong>cardiac enlargement</strong> and <strong>heart failure,</strong> which can present as<strong> arrhythmias </strong>and are consistent with the <strong>patient&#39;s symptoms</strong> and <strong>echocardiogram</strong> findings.<strong> Keshan disease </strong>was <strong>first identified</strong> in regions of<strong> China </strong>with<strong> low selenium soil</strong> content.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"PT-BR\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ref</span></u></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"PT-BR\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">: Harper 30/e: p 286, Vasudevan 9/e: p 523.</span></strong></span></span></p>",
