      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">What trace element is a component of the active site of glutathione peroxidase, an enzyme that plays a critical role in protecting cells from oxidative stress?</span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q2797632",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 30591,
      "difficulty_level": "beginner",
      "subjects_id": [
        1
      ],
      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ans. C) Selenium</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option C:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Glutathione peroxidase (GP)&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">is an important <strong>selenium-containing enzyme</strong>, which is present in good quantities in RBC.</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Thyroxine</strong> is converted to <strong>T3 </strong>by <strong>5&rsquo;-de-iodinase</strong>, which is a <strong>selenium</strong> containing enzyme and in <strong>Se deficiency,</strong> this enzyme becomes<strong> inactive,</strong> causing <strong>hypothyroidism</strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Selenium </strong>acts as an <strong>intracellular antioxidant,</strong> which makes them <strong>complementary to vitamin E.</strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Explanation:</span></u></strong><u> </u></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option A. Calcium:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong> Incorrect </strong>because c<strong>alcium is more</strong> commonly involved in <strong>signaling pathways</strong> and <strong>muscle contraction</strong> rather than being a component of<strong> antioxidant enzymes</strong> like <strong>glutathione peroxidase. </strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option B. Iron</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">:<strong> Incorrect</strong> although iron is a component of various <strong>other enzymes </strong>and is important in <strong>oxygen transport and utilization,</strong> it is<strong> not </strong>the<strong> trace element</strong> associated with<strong> glutathione peroxidase. </strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option D. Chromium:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"> <strong>Incorrect</strong> because <strong>chromium </strong>is primarily involved in the <strong>metabolism of carbohydrates</strong> and <strong>lipids</strong> and in <strong>enhancing </strong>the action of <strong>insulin</strong>, <strong>not </strong>in the composition of <strong>glutathione peroxidase.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Educational Objective:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Selenium </strong>is an <strong>essential trace element </strong>that is a key component of the <strong>active site </strong>of <strong>glutathione peroxidase</strong>. This enzyme plays a vital role in <strong>reducing lipid hydroperoxides </strong>to their corresponding <strong>alcohols </strong>and <strong>reducing free hydrogen peroxide </strong>to water, thus <strong>protecting </strong>the <strong>cell </strong>from <strong>oxidative damage</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ref</span></u></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">: Vasudevan 9/e: p 523.</span></strong></span></span></p>",
